title: WHO chief refers to Global Traditional Medicine Centre in India in his address to World Health Assembly
content: By: PTI Geneva May 28, 2024 00:30 IST Follow Us Facebook Twitter whatsapp World Health Organisation chief Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus on Monday referred to the Global Traditional Medicine Centre set up in India and the first global summit on traditional medicine hosted by the country as he underlined that the year 2023 was a productive one in the UN health agency's work supporting access to medicines and other health products. "We also established the Global Traditional Medicine Centre in India, and hosted the first global summit on traditional medicine," Ghebreyesus said in his remarks as he presented his report to the 77th World Health Assembly in Geneva. In March 2022, the Government of India and the UN health agency had signed an agreement to establish the WHO Global Centre for Traditional Medicine. This global knowledge centre for traditional medicine, supported by an investment of USD 250 million from India, aims to harness the potential of traditional medicine from across the world through modern science and technology to improve the health of people and the planet, the UN health agency had said in a press release at the time. Prime Minister Narendra Modi had said the agreement between the Ministry of Ayush and WHO to establish the Global Centre for Traditional Medicine (GCTM) - world's first - at Jamnagar, Gujarat, is a commendable initiative. He laid the foundation stone of WHO-GCTM in Jamnagar in April 2022. Speaking on the occasion, Modi had said that the WHO-GCTM is recognition of India's contribution and potential in this field. "India's traditional medicine system is not limited only to treatment. It is a holistic science of life. India takes this partnership as a huge responsibility for serving the entire humanity.” WHO had convened the Traditional Medicine Global Summit in August last year in Gandhinagar, Gujarat. The summit was co-hosted by India, which held the G20 presidency in 2023. It was held alongside the G20 Health Ministerial meeting. The summit explored the role of traditional, complementary, and integrative medicine in addressing pressing health challenges and driving progress in global health and sustainable development. Ghebreyesus had arrived in Gujarat to attend the global summit on traditional medicine and was accorded a warm welcome. Praising India for its "rich history" of traditional medicine like Ayurveda and yoga, Ghebreyesus had stressed the need to integrate this ancient medicinal knowledge into the national health system of countries. "India has a rich history of traditional medicine through Ayurveda, including yoga, which has been shown to be effective in alleviating pain. The Gujarat Declaration, the main outcome of this summit, will focus on integration of traditional medicines in national health systems, and help unlock the power of traditional medicine through science," the WHO chief had said. In his address to the World Health Assembly Monday, Ghebreyesus said 2023 was a year of many challenges, but also of many achievements. He said the year 2023 was a productive one in WHO's work supporting access to medicines and other health products. "We prequalified 120 medicines, vaccines, diagnostics and other products last year for HIV, malaria, multidrug-resistant TB, Ebola, polio and Covid-19, as well as the first long-acting insulin analogues,” he said. He noted that one of the biggest disruptions caused by the Covid-19 pandemic was to routine immunization programmes in many countries, resulting in backsliding coverage and outbreaks of measles, diphtheria, polio, yellow fever and more. "In April last year, we launched 'The Big Catch Up' with UNICEF and Gavi, to support countries to shut down outbreaks and restore immunization programmes at least to pre-pandemic levels,” he said. In May last year, the WHO chief had declared an end to both Covid-19 and mpox as global health emergencies. “We continue to call on all countries to maintain and reinforce the capacities for surveillance, detection and response that they built during the pandemic. These investments must not go to waste.” © IE Online Media Services Pvt Ltd First uploaded on: 28-05-2024 at 00:30 IST Here’s Your Exclusive Pass To Premium Stories CLAIM NOW Deepak Tijori on not asking Shah Rukh Khan, Aamir Khan for help Entertainment May 16, 2024 08:01 IST Deepak Tijori, a veteran actor and filmmaker, spoke about his 30-year journey in the industry and the challenges faced by independent producers. He discusses the impact of the star system on film distribution and his preference for unconventional stories. Despite having superstar connections, he prioritised charting his own path. title: Rafael Nadal says it is ‘difficult, not smart’ to play Wimbledon, repeats Olympics ambition after French Open loss
content: After suffering his earliest-ever defeat at the French Open, a tournament he has won a record 14 times, Rafael Nadal said it is unlikely for him to play at Wimbledon next month, even as he eyes a chance to turn out at the Olympics, taking place at his beloved Roland Garros later this year, one last time. “I can’t confirm anything, but I don’t think it’s smart (to play Wimbledon) after everything my body has been through,” he was quoted as saying by AFP at his post-match press conference. “It will be difficult playing on grass, considering that right after Wimbledon are the Olympic Games.” Nadal, hoping to be competitive in his first round against an in-form opponent, showed invariable signs of rustiness after playing only 15 matches since the start of 2023. He bowed out 3-6, 6-7(5), 3-6 to in-form fourth seed Alexander Zverev. The Spaniard was competitive, especially in the second set which he served for before slumping in the tie-breaker, but Zverev’s shotmaking, fitness and power proved too much to handle. Advertisement READ | French Open: Clay god Rafael Nadal’s exit starts end of unprecedented Roland Garros stronghold Nadal said his body had been through the wringer in recent times. “My body has been a jungle for two years. It has been a big fight, waking up as if a snake or a tiger had bitten me. I need to prepare myself and clear my ideas about a calendar. My main goal is to prepare for the Olympics and to prepare well to be healthy here,” he said, per tennismajors.com, at the press conference. The soon-to-be-38-year-old said he takes positives from Monday’s loss to the German. “My feeling is that I wasn’t that far. I was at a good level (in the match),” Nadal added. “If it was the last time I played here, I would be at peace with myself. I tried to do everything I could to play here. At least I did. Even if I lost, that’s part of the business... I don’t know what’s going to happen in the next few months.” Nadal also had the unusual experience of being watched by active players, in competition at the French Open this year, who were in attendance at Court Philippe Chatrier to bear witness to his potentially final outing. “Happy that it happens, it means that I have a positive legacy here,” he said.

title: School curriculum: Maharashtra govt scraps Manusmriti reference from draft
content: The Maharashtra government will not proceed with all the recommendations from the recently proposed Maharashtra State Curriculum Framework for School Education, said State Education Minister Deepak Kesarkar. The framework had stirred a controversy for using lines from Manusmriti as reference in one of the chapters in the draft, a move that Kesarkar clarified had not received governmental or the steering committee’s approval before being made public. Speaking at a press conference in Mumbai on Thursday, Kesarkar expressed regret in excluding Marathi as a compulsory language. “It happened because the draft was made public without following the proper procedure,” he said. Advertisement Kesarkar also said that the exclusion of English as a compulsory language for Class 11 and 12 was “because the government is working to offer higher education in regional languages, including technical education”. After the minister’s clarification, the SCERT issued a press release late Monday stating that Marathi and English language would be compulsory from Class 1 to 10. It also clarified that Hindi, Sanskrit and other Indian and foreign languages are being offered from Class 6, while Classes 11 and 12 students will have to learn two languages — one Indian and the other foreign. Last week, the State Council of Educational Research and Training unveiled the new Maharashtra State Curriculum Framework (SCF), advocating the integration of Indian Knowledge System (IKS) into School Education (SE). It proposed including texts such as the Bhagavad Gita and Manache Shlok — a composition by Samarth Ramdas Swami — for memorisation enhancement through recitation competitions. A chapter on “value education and disposition” from SCF, which aimed at character-building for students, sparked controversy as it began with a Sanskrit verse from Manusmriti, an ancient Hindu legal text describing the social system. This inclusion drew criticism from various quarters regarding the intent behind the decision. Advertisement Kesarkar addressed the issue, stating, “It was an error on the part of the steering committee that placed the draft in public domain without state government approval. The people involved have expressed regret for this. Let me make it clear, the government does not want to propagate any text and will not include any of this in textbooks.” After the matter came to light, several educationists questioned the decision to the Manusmriti reference. “There are numerous Sanskrit verses conveying similar meanings, yet the draft selects one from Manusmriti. This decision appears either politically naive or intentionally provocative, potentially offending certain segments of the society,” said a renowned educationist. While language policy for Classes 3 to 10 lacked clarity; for Classes 11 and 12, English was categorised as foreign language. Chhagan Bhujbal, Maharashtra Cabinet Minister, also expressed concerns, saying the inclusion of Manusmriti in the curriculum could send a wrong signal among Dalits and OBCs. “Such actions could impact us electorally. This initiative must be halted. Though seemingly insignificant now, it could pose future challenges,” Bhujbal said.

title: Tech Roundup: Climate change disinformation, a practical example
creator: Fabiane Ziolla Menezes
description: The post Tech Roundup: Climate change disinformation, a practical example appeared first on The Brazilian Report.
content: Welcome to our Tech Roundup, where we bring you the biggest stories in technology and innovation in Brazil and Latin America. This week: The impacts of climate misinformation and disinformation campaigns have never been more present. Between late April and early May, Rio Grande do Sul, Brazil’s southernmost state, was hit by unprecedented floods. More than 70 percent of the state’s almost 500 municipalities were affected, and nearly 70,000 people are still in temporary shelters. In addition to the natural impacts of the tragedy, authorities, volunteers, and the population are having to deal with a wave of disinformation and misinformation campaigns on social media. State of play. In the first weeks of the tragedy, several false reports claimed that bureaucracy was holding up food, water, and clothing donations. Most came from civilians in or near the flooded areas (the majority of them supporters of the former president in one way or another) and right-wing social influencers. Yes, but ... Elected officials also spread some of them, as is the case with Congressman Eduardo Bolsonaro, the son of former President Jair Bolsonaro and a representative of Steve Bannon’s far-far-right movement in Brazil. By the numbers. As the catastrophe evolved and the situation became more serious, false narratives proliferated. A study by NetLab, an internet and social media research laboratory at the Federal University of Rio de Janeiro, identified at least eight fake news narratives on social media posts and ads. title: Caribbean leader blasts 'empty' climate promises at small islands summit
creator: Reuters
description: The president of this decade's summit for Small Island Developing States on Monday blasted "empty" and "grossly inadequate" climate pledges, saying wealthy nations have failed to meet obligations to limit damages from carbon emissions. Small island states across the Pacific, Atlantic and Caribbean, with negligible emissions, are particularly vulnerable to economic crises and rising temperatures due to their exposure to natural disasters, high debt and reliance on imports and tourism. The Atlantic hurricane season, starting in June is expected to be more active than usual due to near-record warm Atlantic Ocean temperatures and cooler surface water in the Pacific.

title: Make reasonable policy, stall removal for time being: HC to CIDCO after plea by hoarding owners
content: The Bombay High Court on Monday asked CIDCO to stall its move to remove the hoarding concerned and instead suggested they come up with a policy or regime for hoardings located within their jurisdiction or area. The court was hearing a plea by advertisement agencies challenging the notices issued by City and Industrial Development Corporation (CIDCO) to remove alleged illegal hoardings in Navi Mumbai Airport Influence Notified Area (NAINA). A vacation bench of Justices NR Borkar and Somasekhar Sundaresan also remarked that civic authorities said nothing to the advertising firms until the Ghatkopar hoarding collapse incident. Firms including Devangi Outdoor Advertising and Harmesh Dilip Tanna, proprietor of Gargee Graphics, had approached the High Court stating that CIDCO did not have the jurisdiction to send such notices. The petitioners claimed they had erected the hoardings legally after obtaining necessary permissions from authorities. Advertisement Despite this, they said they have received notices for removal of hoardings within 24 hours or face action under Maharashtra Regional and Town Planning Act (MRTP). As per petitioners, the authorities have warned them that if hoardings were not removed, they would dismantle them and recover costs from the owner. The notices by CIDCO come in wake of the collapse of a hoarding on a petrol pump in Ghatkopar on May 13, which killed 17 people. CIDCO purportedly issued notices to several hoarding owners after the unfortunate incident. Advocate for the petitioner firms, Mohsin Khan, argued that the notices were issued without a show-cause notice, which violated the principles of natural justice. Khan also claimed that authorities failed to verify the structural stability of the hoardings before issuing the notice, hence the action amounted to being arbitrary and ex-facie illegal. However, CIDCO’s lawyer submitted that the authority had issued notices to several owners of hoardings after discovering they had been installed without requisite permissions. The lawyer claimed that the same exercise was crucial as it was within the Navi Mumbai airport region. The corporation also claimed that the hoardings erected since 2018–19 had applied for permission in 2023, including those by the petitioners. Advertisement The bench sought to know if the authority had conducted any structural audit of all hoardings within its domain, and whether the authority was planning to bring a regime or policy in place for illegal hoardings within its area. These hoardings are not brought back to CIDCO, the bench said, and until the Ghatkopar incident, nobody said anything. In these circumstances, the bench asked if the corporation should at least not study whether the hoardings pose any danger, instead of bringing them down? “Have a reasonable policy view, otherwise case by case people will come. If you decide to demolish everything, that is also different. We are placing this on May 30. Till next date, if it is not pulled down, we are asking you to hold it,” the bench said.

content: , /PRNewswire/ -- "I wanted to provide golfers with a modified surface that would replicate the feel and action of sand in a sand trap," said an inventor, from Denison, , "so I invented the SPLASH MAT. My design would offer a more realistic alternative to conventional practice mats." The patent-pending invention provides an effective practice mat for golfers. In doing so, it offers a realistic simulation of sand trap shots. As a result, it eliminates the need to climb in an out of a sand trap when practicing. It also could enhance performance. The invention features a practical design that is easy to use so it is ideal for golfers. Additionally, a prototype model is available upon request. The original design was submitted to the sales office of InventHelp. It is currently available for licensing or sale to manufacturers or marketers. title: INEC Commences Voter Registration Process In Edo
creator: Ikenna Ngere
description: The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) commenced the Continuous Voter Registration exercise in Edo State on Monday. The exercise aims to capture would-be voters who have yet to register ahead of the governorship election in Edo on September 21. Naija News gathered that the CVR and the PVC collection would be a 10-day exercise from May 27 [...]The post INEC Commences Voter Registration Process In Edo appeared first on Naija News.
content: The Independent National Electoral Commission ( INEC ) commenced the Continuous Voter Registration exercise in Edo State on Monday. The exercise aims to capture would-be voters who have yet to register ahead of the governorship election in Edo on September 21. Naija News gathered that the CVR and the PVC collection would be a 10-day exercise from May 27 to June 5, 2024, from 9 am to 3 pm daily, including weekends. Despite a call from the state acting chairman of the All Progressives Congress, Jarret Tenebe, on Friday, to cancel the exercise due to the damage to its secretariat, materials, and equipment meant for CVR, it proceeded as scheduled. In response to the call, Edo INEC’s head of Voters Education and Publicity, Timidi Wariowei, expressed dissatisfaction, stating that it is unjust to accuse the electoral body in this manner. The CVR exercise, monitored in Oredo, Egor, and Ikpoba-Okha local governments, indicated that PVC collection was also progressing alongside the continuous voter registration exercise. At the registration site in Ikpoba-Okha, Rhoda Gumus, the INEC National Commissioner overseeing Edo, Delta, and Cross River, expressed contentment with the ongoing exercise and urged registrants to wait patiently as their registrations were processed. Gumus said, “ We have been to Oredo, and we are here at the Ikpoba-Okha registration area, which we are using as our state head office registration centre because of the flood disaster that happened at our head office on Friday. “We are in touch with other registration areas within and outside Benin, and the exercise is going on smoothly. As you can see, we have registered some people, and others are still waiting. The process just started today. It is impressive and commendable . “ The state Resident Electoral Commissioner, Anugbum Onuoha, affirmed that INEC was adequately prepared for the exercise, emphasizing that the flood disaster, which damaged some of the commission’s equipment, would not hinder the operation. Onuoha said, “ We thank God for the enablement to begin this exercise, having in mind the flood disaster that destroyed some of our equipment on Friday. Due to the flood disaster, we moved our head office registration area to the INEC office at Ikpoba-Okha local government. “We are here and witnessing a large turnout of people who are here as either new registrants or to transfer their registration or for PVC collection. INEC is prepared for this exercise and nothing will make us fail. People expected us to discontinue the exercise but we were prepared even before the flood disaster happened. “Yes, we had some initial network problems, but it has been resolved, and the exercise is going on smoothly, and by the grace of God, the exercise will be successful .”

It is understood that the Brazilian is set to leave Spurs over the next few months, and Milan, who are in the market for a right-back, have been now. He is, however, not the only right-back that Milan have been evaluating, according to . title: Junior Pope’s wife: Police confirm arrest of ‘blogger who defamed E-Money’
creator: Olalekan Olabulo
description: Tribune OnlineJunior Pope’s wife: Police confirm arrest of ‘blogger who defamed E-Money’The Nigeria Police, Lagos State Command, has confirmed the arrest of an online blogger, identified as Stanley Okoruwa for allegedly defaming a businessman, Emeka Okonkwo, popularly known as “E-Money”. The suspect, who was paraded before newsmen on Monday, confessed to the crime and claimed to have used the offending video to boost his followership online. [...]Junior Pope’s wife: Police confirm arrest of ‘blogger who defamed E-Money’Tribune Online
content: The Nigeria Police, Lagos State Command, has confirmed the arrest of an online blogger, identified as Stanley Okoruwa for allegedly defaming a businessman, Emeka Okonkwo, popularly known as “E-Money”. The suspect, who was paraded before newsmen on Monday, confessed to the crime and claimed to have used the offending video to boost his followership online. Okoruwa in the said video accused the businessman of having illicit affairs with the wife of the late Nollywood star, John Odonwodo, aka Junior Pope. He also accused the businessman of being responsible for the death of the late Nollywood star, who died in a boat accident. The spokesperson of the command, Benjamin Hundeyin, told newsmen that the suspect would be prosecuted for cyberbullying and defamation of character. ALSO READ: Junior Pope’s wife: E-money confirms arrest of ‘man who defamed him’ He said that the suspect was arrested in Uromi, Delta State, following a petition from the businessman. Hundeyin said, “He is going to be prosecuted because the things he engaged in were criminal in nature. He has allegedly defamed E-Money and he is going to be prosecuted. “We are not prosecuting the suspect because of the personality involved, but because he has allegedly committed a crime, the personality goes through the normal channel by reporting the case to the police and we investigated and arrested the suspect.” Hundeyin warned social media users against content that is injurious to other people’s personalities, stressing that action may be taken against them if reports of their content were found offensive by anyone. The suspect, while speaking with newsmen, said “I did a video about E-Money. I said a lot of things that are not true in that video, that is why the police arrested me.” He added, “I said something regarding a video I saw online about a woman – saying that Sir E-Money is responsible for the things that happened to Nollywood Actor, John Odonwodo, aka Junior Pope’s case. “I said something like that, I also said that Sir E-Money was also having an affair with Junior Pope’s wife. I have never in my life met E-Money. Everything I made in that video was not true.” Continuing, he said, ” I made the video out of trying to boost my page traffic level, I never knew it would go viral the way it went. I don’t have a bad intention to spoil Sir E-Money’s name. I was just making the video, I didn’t know it would go such wide.” “I know the contents of the video were wrong of me to have made. I don’t know the video will escalate to that extent,” the suspect added. Stanley stated, ” I saw that the video was already going viral, I thought pulling it down will not make sense. I decided to leave it. I have not reached out to E-Money to apologise, because I don’t have his contact to do so. “I was already planning to make an apology video, that was when I was arrested by the police. I have been praying to have this opportunity to apologize to him. I am very sorry Sir E-Money, I don’t mean to tarnish his image, I didn’t mean to spoil his name online.”

title: Blink Kobs clinch 2024 Uganda Lacrosse League
creator: David Isabirye
description: Blink Kobs players hoist their trophy at MUBS playground, Nakawa" data-medium-file="https://i0.wp.com/kawowo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/WhatsApp-Image-2024-05-27-at-1.44.16-PM.jpeg?fit=480%2C320&ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i0.wp.com/kawowo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/WhatsApp-Image-2024-05-27-at-1.44.16-PM.jpeg?fit=780%2C520&ssl=1" />The 2024 Uganda national lacrosse league successfully climaxed on Saturday, 25th May at the MUBS playground in Nakawa, Kampala city. Blink Kobs lacrosse club won the season, having amassed a total of 18 points from 8 matches played. Six games were won with two losses. FCA Warriors played second fiddle with 16 points. On the [...]The post Blink Kobs clinch 2024 Uganda Lacrosse League appeared first on Kawowo Sports.
content: Benjamin Ojok of champions Blink Kobs Lacrosse club was named as the most valuable player (MVP) of the season for the league organized by Uganda Lacrosse Association (ULA). The 2024 Uganda national lacrosse league successfully climaxed on Saturday, 25th May at the MUBS playground in Nakawa, Kampala city. Blink Kobs lacrosse club won the season, having amassed a total of 18 points from 8 matches played. Six games were won with two losses. FCA Warriors played second fiddle with 16 points. On the final day of the season, Blink Kobs humbled FCA Warriors 18-11. Buroni Panthers finished third (12 points) with zero goal difference, same points as Jinja Nile Zulus who had a deficit of 13 goals. MUBS men finished bottom of the standings with 3 points, attained from their only victory of the campaign, 23-20 over Jinja Nile Zulus. Benjamin Ojok of champions Blink Kobs was named as the most valuable player (MVP) of the season. The league top scorer was Owen Waluku of MUBS men lacrosse club with 56 goals. Waluku also garnered the most points of the season, 66 as well as the most supportive member accolade. The best goalkeeper was Moses Owen Afoyrwoth (FCA Warriors) with 41%. Another FCA Warriors player, Timothy Munage was the most improved player. Bernard Otim (Jinja Nile Zulus) won the fair-play award whilst Amis Kisige (FCA Warriors) took the brave heart accolade. The league was organized by Uganda Lacrosse Association (ULA).

title: Scooter crashes into Taurus truck; father dies, son injured
description: THRISSUR: A man was killed and his son was injured after a scooter crashed into the back of a Taurus truck.
content: THRISSUR: A man was killed and his son was injured after a scooter crashed into the back of a Taurus truck. The incident took place in Irinjalakuda in Thrissur. The deceased has been identified as Mapranam native Shaiju (43). He is the brother of Irinjalakuda municipality councillor Baiju Kuttikadan. The accident took place on Sunday night. According to sources, the scooter in which Shaiju and his son were travelling rammed into the back of the Taurus truck which was parked near Mapranam junction. Although Shaiju was immediately rushed to the hospital, his life could not be saved. Shaiju's son Edwin Antony is undergoing treatment at the intensive care unit of a private hospital in Thrissur. Shaiju's funeral will be held on Tuesday at 11 am at Mapranam Holy Cross Pilgrimage Shrine.

title: Mayor-Driver spat: Police confirm evidence to support Mayor's claim
description: THIRUVANANTHAPURAM: The cantonment assistant commissioner confirmed receiving strong evidence to support the mayor's complaint.
content: THIRUVANANTHAPURAM: The police recreated the mayor-KSRTC driver feud according to the complaint about the KSRTC bus driver not allowing the Mayor’s car to pass through. The complaint also alleged that the driver showed obscene gestures at the family members. The trip was recreated four days ago to confirm the allegations against driver Yadhu. On the 25th, the police travelled from Plamoodu to PMG by driving a bus, followed by a car at the same time. The cantonment assistant commissioner confirmed receiving strong evidence to support the mayor's complaint. The police found that the person in the back seat of the car could see the driver making obscene gestures. The Cantonment Police had registered a case against Yadhu for insulting women. The Assistant Commissioner stated that it is customary to record mahazar in such cases. Apart from the mayor, her husband Sachin Dev MLA, Arya's brother and sister-in-law were also in the car. Their car, which was returning after the wedding reception, was not given space by the KSRTC bus. The mayor’s car then blocked the bus in front of the Palayam shopping complex and she alleged the driver of reckless driving and also making obscene gestures. Passengers stated that Sachin Dev boarded the bus during an argument with the bus driver. The conductor's trip sheet also says that Sachin boarded the bus. However, Sachin told the police that he did not board the bus and did not disrupt the service.

title: Paris Hilton vacations with rarely-seen brother Barron and his wife Tessa in Maui as fans gush ‘the family is so cute’
creator: Dan Roberts
content: PARIS Hilton has shown off her growing babies while on a family vacation in Hawai'i. The reality star and socialite was joined by her rarely seen brother, Barron, and his own wife and kids. Paris and Barron reunited for a relaxing vacation at the Grand Wailea resort in Maui . The 43-year-old shared a series of photos and videos from her trip to her Instagram. Paris smiled as she relaxed on a pink bed, in pink loungewear, while cuddling with her kids . She shares two children with husband Carter Reum - a son named Phoenix and a daughter London . She is also step-mom to Carter's older daughter, Evie, from his previous relationship with Laura Bellizzi. Joining them on the trip, and appearing in a family photo, was brother Barron, his wife, Tessa, and their kids. "Reliving my childhood and carrying on our family vacation tradition at the @GrandWailea with my beautiful family," Paris captioned the collection. In the comments section, fans lauded the hotel heiress and her children. "Most beautiful family," one person commented, as another echoed, "I cannot handle the cuteness." "Being a mom is by far your greatest look," a third noted. While a fourth gushed, "London is SO CUTE!!!! I don’t have enough available brain cells to process." As one person complimented, "I am so happy for Paris because she got everything she ever wished for." Paris better enjoy her vacations while she can, because she will soon be getting back to work on a new reality show. Being a mom is by far your greatest look." And she'll do so with Nicole Richie , 42, more than 20 years after their first paired outing. The iconic duo previously worked together from 2003 to 2007 on The Simple Life . Paris teased her reality return on Instagram, posting a video of a classic television broadcasting static noise. Suddenly, Paris and Nicole's voices could be heard singing, and then yelling their personal theme song, Sanasa. "New Era. Same Besties," she captioned. "Coming soon to Peacock." Earlier this month, Paris and Nicole teased something was in the works when they posted a collage of different milestone events throughout their friendship, including early 2000s selfies and childhood snaps. "From Day 1: Sill and Bill," they captioned their posts, referring to the nicknames they gave one another on The Simple Life. Once the news was official , fans online went wild. "A pop culture renaissance!!!!!!!!!!!!!!" one person exclaimed. "The OGs of reality show!!" another declared. "The real celebrities we love!! Yaaaas!! Can’t wait queens. "So f**king excited!," a third added. "I have no words but Slivin. That’s Hot!" Paris and Nicole became household names, and punchlines, nearly two decades ago, as their reality show, The Simple Life followed the two high-end celebs experiencing life outside their bubble by working low-paying jobs . The first season aired in 2003, and documented Paris and Nicole's one-month stay in Arkansas with a farm family. A year later, the besties headed out in a pink pickup truck where they participated in many different jobs, including fishing and working as maids, for Season 2. During Season 3, the iconic duo worked several different internships across the United States , and in Season 4, they took on the role of being wives in a family. In the final season, Paris and Nicole worked at a summer camp as counselors.

title: Emmerdale’s Tom King targets second victim after Belle ‘exit’ – and it’s sickening
creator: Calli Kitson
description: He wants them to seriously suffer.
content: Tom King ( James Chase ) reached another shocking low in Monday’s (May 27) episode of Emmerdale as he prepared to poison Piper the dog. Tom is currently on his own in the village due to Belle ( Eden Taylor-Draper ) spending time in a mental health unit. This development happened last week, when Belle spoke to a nurse and said she knows her mental health is struggling, and is worried about what may happen next. We know that Belle’s difficulties with her mental health are being exacerbated as a result of Tom’s abusive behaviour. During Tom’s latest plan of making it seem as though Belle was the one with anger problems, he wound her up so much, Belle pushed him to the floor in front of Rhona (Zoe Henry), Marlon (Mark Charnock) and Vanessa ( Michelle Hardwick ). In tonight’s episode of the ITV soap, Tom spent time with Lydia (Karen Blick). As they chatted about Belle, Tom learnt that his wife had asked Lydia to visit her. Lydia tried to tell Tom that Belle probably didn’t want him to see her in a dark place. Out of control, Tom had to come up with another plan – and it was horrific. title: Emmerdale ‘confirms’ who will expose Tom – as surprise newcomer enters the frame
creator: Calli Kitson
description: Saved at last?
content: Belle Dingle ( Eden Taylor-Draper ) had a meeting with her therapist in Monday’s (May 27) episode of Emmerdale. Last week, Belle decided to check into a mental health unit. As a result of Tom’s ( James Chase ) abusive behaviour, poor Belle is now struggling and decided time away from the village would be safer for her. Watching Belle drive away was challenging for Tom – and not because he found it difficult to see his wife in a dark place. All alone and surrounded by professionals who want to help her, Belle could end up telling someone about her abusive relationship – and an out of control Tom knew he had to do something about it. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a webbrowser that supports HTML5video Unable to visit Belle because she asked Lydia (Karen Blick) to see her instead, Tom developed a plan in the hope his wife would return home – and it involved poisoning Piper the dog. Meanwhile, in the mental health unit, Belle was speaking with her therapist. Belle started the session feeling a little puzzled. She said how in the past, when she experienced problems with her mental health, she would hear voices in her head – and that isn’t happening this time. Continuing to open up, it became apparent that Belle believed every recent thing she’d been through with Tom were all her fault. She said she makes Tom feel like he isn’t good enough and thought he had to prove himself just so they could share a house together. Belle’s therapist then put forward the theory her relapses happen as a result of triggers within relationships. ‘You think Tom’s the problem?’, Belle asked. ‘Do you think he is?’, the therapist responded. At this point, a fearful and anxious Belle said no, but then ‘I don’t know’ immediately after. title: Major Emmerdale twist as two unlikely residents are in cahoots to destroy Kim Tate
creator: Calli Kitson
description: Huge shock!
content: It’s been confirmed that Ruby Fox-Miligan ( Beth Cordingly ) and Rose Jackson (Christine Tremarco) are working together in Emmerdale to destroy Kim Tate ( Claire King ). Up until Monday’s (May 27) episode, we’ve known Rose as simply Dawn’s ( Olivia Bromley ) estranged mother – and someone who is annoying Kim a great deal. All she’s been doing for the past few weeks is trying to develop a connection with Dawn and enjoying Kim’s posh drinks tray – but it seems that’s all set to change from here on in. After a brief interaction between Rose and Ruby in the pub, which established they know each other somehow, they then met up at the graveyard. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a webbrowser that supports HTML5video Rose alluded to the fact she didn’t want to be a part of Ruby’s plan anymore, because Dawn’s son Evan is poorly and it was making her feel terrible. Ruby told her friend that once their revenge is complete, she’ll be able to be a mum to Dawn – something she’s always wanted. So, what’s the plan? Split Kim and Will (Dean Andrews) up, let Ruby take Home Farm (something Caleb (William Ash) believes belongs to them anyway) and allow Rose to emotionally support Dawn when everything falls apart. It appears Ruby has been secretly developing quite the plot on behalf of her husband, who’s own plan to destroy Kim Tate failed spectacularly last year. But will it work this time? title: Transfer news LIVE! Man United want Chelsea star, McKenna decision; Arsenal in £43m battle; Toney to Spurs
creator: George Flood
description: Stay up to date with the latest transfer news, rumours and gossip all summer
content: Sport | Football Transfer news LIVE! Arsenal are keen to strengthen in attack, as they prepare for another busy summer transfer window. The Gunners are reportedly in a battle with Bayern Munich and Barcelona for £43m-rated Nico Williams, while Newcastle star Alexander Isak has been linked too. It is also claimed they will contend too with Tottenham and Manchester United for French starlet Desire Doue. United are eyeing defensive reinforcements, with Chelsea ’s Levi Colwill said to be on the shortlist. Chelsea are hoping to sign both Crystal Palace winger Michael Olise and Burnley goalkeeper James Trafford, though need a new manager first as they close in on top target Enzo Maresca of Leicester in the race to succeed Mauricio Pochettino, who, along with Thomas Frank, has been sounded out to potentially replace Erik ten Hag at Old Trafford with a decision over the Dutchman’s future expected this week following an end-of-season review. Kieran McKenna is now understood to be out of the race , but Roberto De Zerbi is an option. Tottenham are said to be lining up the likes of Ivan Toney, Jarrad Branthwaite and Evanilson as part of ambitious summer plans, while Liverpool could look to make either Leny Yoro or Leeds winger Crysencio Summerville their first signing under new boss Arne Slot. Follow all the latest transfer news, rumours and gossip live below! Latest transfer news and rumours Live updates Ivan Toney is available for between £30-40million this summer. That’s according to TEAMtalk, with it claimed that Brentford have been forced to lower their valuation as the striker enters the final 12 months of his contract. Ange Postecoglou is believed to have urged Tottenham to sign a striker this window, with Toney high on the wishlist, and a reduced asking price has significantly improved Spurs’ hopes of getting their man. Barcelona and Bayern Munich are among the clubs interested in a summer move for Nico Williams. Recent reports have suggested Arsenal are very keen on the 21-year-old, who plays for Athletic Bilbao and is believed to have a release clause of around £43m. However, according to Relevo, Bayern are eyeing Williams and will monitor him at the Euros, while Barcelona have long admired the winger. Levi Colwill is among the centre-backs being considered by Manchester United. The Daily Star claim that United are refusing to meet Everton’s £80m asking price for Jarrad Branthwaite, and will be on if it is not lowered to around £60m. It’s suggested that other targets being lined up are Chelsea’s Colwill, Marc Guehi and Juventus defender Gleison Bremer. One manager not on the move this summer is Unai Emery. The Aston Villa boss has signed a new five-year contract, after leading the club into the Champions League. His time in England with Arsenal didn’t work out, but Emery is evidently loving life at Villa, committing his future through to 2029. Sofyan Amrabat has indicated that he could yet stay at Manchester United this summer. The Moroccan midfielder has endured a difficult season-long loan spell at Old Trafford from Serie A side Fiorentina, starting only 10 matches in the Premier League and limited to a lot of substitute cameos under Erik ten Hag. However, Amrabat’s influence grew as he showed signs of improvement during the final stages of the season, starting the last three Premier League matches and also Saturday’s surprise 2-1 victory over champions Manchester City in a memorable FA Cup final triumph at Wembley that guaranteed Europa League qualification for next term. Amrabat’s previous struggles to convince during a season that resulted in an eighth-place Premier League finish - their worst league position for 34 years - had led many to believe that there was very little chance of United exercising their €25million (£21m) option to sign him on a permanent basis this summer, having already spent €10m (£8m) on the initial loan deal. However, his recent resurgence could have changed minds. "Do I already know what I’m going to do next year? No. We are going to talk," he told Dutch outlet Ziggo Sport. "Staying is certainly an option. Look, I think it has been a very difficult season. For Manchester United it needs to be much better, and also for me personally." Read more on that here! The manager fun continues... Graham Potter has been out of management since he was sacked by Chelsea, after what proved to be a disastrous move from Brighton. The Guardian report that Potter is now in contention for a Premier League return... with Brighton. The Seagulls are on the hunt for a new manager after Roberto De Zerbi’s departure, and Potter is being considered Kieran McKenna is increasingly likely to remain at Ipswich. The Athletic report that McKenna is now expected to sign a long-term contract, ensuring he will lead the club in the Premier League next season. Chelsea have already moved on, but McKenna was still a target for Manchester United and Brighton. Newcastle are considering a move for Burnley goalkeeper James Trafford. Recent reports have suggested Chelsea are keen on Trafford, who was recently named in England’s pre-Euro 2024 training squad and is believed to be valued at around £20m. However, the Mail report that Newcastle are also now considering a move, after refusing to meet Arsenal’s £30m asking price for Aaron Ramsdale. Kevin De Bruyne, Ederson and Bernardo Silva all face uncertain futures at Manchester City. The Times report that Ederson and De Bruyne are both attracting interest from clubs in Saudi Arabia. Ederson in particular could be persuaded to make the move, it is suggested, while De Bruyne is a target as he enters the final 12 months of his current contract. Silva will be allowed to leave this summer if City receive a £50m offer. PSG and Barcelona are both keen, but the Spanish side are unlikely to be able to afford the fee. Over to the latest on Manchester United’s managerial situation now. We know that Erik ten Hag’s Old Trafford future will be determined this week during an end-of-season review by the club, with speculation that he is still likely to be removed despite Saturday’s FA Cup success at Wembley making it an obviously more difficult decision. However, the Manchester Evening News now report that United are actually considering keeping Ten Hag for next season, informing the representatives of potential new managerial candidates that they have not ruled out retaining their current boss. Ten Hag has one year left to run on the three-year contract he signed after swapping Ajax for United in the summer of 2022, with the Red Devils possessing the option to trigger a further 12 months beyond that. The plot thickens... Have your say...

title: Accidental fire closes popular Clinton Township diner
creator: Mitch Hotts
description: Co-owner Zef Camaj vows to reopen the diner on Hayes Road between 17 Mile and 18 Mile roads once the building is repaired. "When we do, we will be better than ever," he said.
content: A kitchen fire that broke out over the weekend has forced the closure of a popular Clinton Township diner. The fire at Ken’s Country Kitchen in the Amore Plaza shopping center on Hayes Road was reported after 3 p.m. Sunday, a short time after the employees had left the building for the day, the owner says. Zef Camaj, who co-owns the restaurant with Alex Gjelaj, said before workers left, they had thoroughly cleaned the kitchen. He suspects one worker may have accidentally knocked a pilot on a grill, which eventually sparked the blaze. “The thing is, we recently completed a remodeling of the building, completely revamped it,” Camaj said. “We couldn’t make it better than it was.” Clinton Township Fire Department administrators were not available to comment Monday because of the holiday. The diner was known for its breakfast dishes, Camaj said. Ken’s Country Kitchen was a consistent winner in the Macomb Daily’s annual reader’s choice contest, and had also won similar contests with the Detroit Free Press and WDIV-TV (Channel 4). “The lucky part is, no one was inside when this happened, so nobody was injured. We are happy about that,” Camaj added. Ken’s Country Kitchen had originally opened in the 1990s at the Clinton Township location. In recent years, the partner decided to venture out to the northern part of the county, and opened one on Main Street, north of Division Road (32 Mile Road) in Richmond. The owners say they are offering some of the 20 employees work at the Richmond location until the Clinton Township one is refurbished. When that will be obviously isn’t known at this point. The eatery must deal with its insurance carrier on the damage and related details before it can plan on repairing the facility. “Hello, we will be closed until further notice,” the owner posted on his Facebook page. “We will keep you updated as soon as we know more details.” Camaj also urges Clinton Township customers to drive out to Richmond to enjoy the home cooking they have come to enjoy. “I can tell you this: We will reopen and when we do, we will be better than ever,” he said.

title: Attorney-general, Abaribe, others oppose replacement of national anthem
creator: Dennis Erezi
description: The move by the National Assembly to replace the current national anthem with the former one through an expeditious legislative process suffered a setback on Monday. Attorney General of the Federation and Minister of Justice, Lateef Fagbemi, who attended a public hearing on the matter organized by the Senate Committee on Judiciary, Human Rights and [...]The post Attorney-general, Abaribe, others oppose replacement of national anthem appeared first on The Guardian Nigeria News - Nigeria and World News.
content: The move by the National Assembly to replace the current national anthem with the former one through an expeditious legislative process suffered a setback on Monday. Attorney General of the Federation and Minister of Justice, Lateef Fagbemi, who attended a public hearing on the matter organized by the Senate Committee on Judiciary, Human Rights and Legal Matters, warned that the issue of the National Anthem, should not be treated with legislative fiat. He said as commendable as the move by both Chambers of the National Assembly may be, enacting a law on National Anthem or replacing the current with the old demands that, Nigerians are carried along. Fagbemi said: “In some cases, national anthem emerges from open national competition among interested citizens. In other instances, the proposed national anthem is subjected to plebiscite or referendum, before its eventual adoption or declaration. He argued that “The essence of the foregoing is to secure the buy-in and confidence of the people and to ensure that the anthem meets their collective aspirations and suits their contemporary socio-political conditions.” “Against the background of the foregoing, I am of the considered opinion that the revered issue of choice of a national item should not come into being only by legislative fiat, or presidential proclamation alone. According to him, “the decision to change Nigeria’s National Anthem whether by replacing it with the old one or a new one, should be subjected to a wider process of citizen participation through zonal public hearings, resolutions of the Federal Executive Council, Council of State, National and State Assemblies, etc. “The outcome of this process is bound to be a true reflection of the wishes of the generality or majority of Nigerians.” Former minority leader of the Senate, Eyinnaya Abaribe, said he was totally against the move because the second stanza of the National Anthem is the country’s national prayer. He also revealed that his senatorial district was totally against the move, as there are more pressing issues that require the attention of the Federal Government. He said: “While we support the efforts of the Federal Government under President Bola A. Tinubu to ameliorate the difficulties that Nigerians face today of biting inflation, crippling unemployment and widespread insecurity, we do not feel that it is a priority to embark on a homegrown National Anthem 46 years after its adoption by Nigerians. “The reasons given for such unseemly haste to revert back to the colonial era anthem ark rather nebulous and mostly self-serving. “Reverting to an anthem that harks back to our troubled past as a nation does not enhance unity. Rather it reminds us all of nomenclatures such as ‘Tribes, Tongues’, Natives’ which divides us as a nation and which led to the unfortunate civil war. “The present anthem has a second stanza that is used as our National Prayer. Thus, going back to the old anthem will make the nation be put even further apart as it will mean we will not have a National Prayer. The lawmaker contended that the present National Anthem was accompanied by a pledge which all children and patriots recite at official functions. “Will reverting back to the old anthem not mean abrogation of the pledge since they go together? He queried. “The peoples of Abia South Senatorial District are desirous of policies and plans to reduce the pump price of petrol from the present 1.000 naira per litre in Aba, the 224 naira per kWh of electricity, the more than 100% increase in food prices than going back to an anthem written by a colonial citizen of Britain and bequeathed to Nigerians at our independence in 1960. Therefore, the people of Abia South Senatorial District in their entirety reject the bill to revert back to the old anthem.” In his submission at the public hearing , the Minister of Information and National Orientation, Alhaji Mohammed Idris Malagi, recommended that the scope should be expanded to include a robust issue on national identity rather than limiting it to change of national anthem. The Minister who was represented by the Director-General of National Orientation Agency ( NOA) , Mr Lanre Issa-Onilu, noted that some lines in the old national anthem does not make a complete meaning. “The issue of national anthem is just a sub-sect. What we should be looking at is the National Identity Act. “The challenge we have today is that we do not have a value national identity which the national anthem is one of them. It is not about singing in schools, it is about learning it and imbibing it.” Also cautioning the National Assembly on expeditious passage of the bill, Chief Mike Ozekhome (SAN), called for wider consultations for Nigerians to accept whatever National Anthem is proposed and buy into it . According to him, the National Assembly should widen the scope of participation in the process of coming up with such an Act for general acceptability . He however supported the move to replace the current “Arise O Compatriots National Anthem” with the “Nigeria, We Hail Thee”, the country started with, in October 1960. He said such a move was long overdue since the current National Anthem adopted in 1978 , does not have the required gravitas and not inspirational to fire the passion and zeal for Nationhood among Nigerians. Nigeria, according to him, will not be the first country in the world to replace current National Anthem with the old one as over 20 countries like Russia, Austria, Chile, France, Saudi Arabia, China, Brazil, Iran, Iraq etc, have done so at different times in the past. title: Was Johnny Wactor Married? Wife, Family Details and Cause of Death Revealed
creator: Shazmeen Navrange
description: Johnny Wactor’s death has left many deeply shocked. content: Was Johnny Wactor Married? Wife, Family Details and Cause of Death Revealed By Johnny Wactor’s death has left many deeply shocked. The talented actor was most well known for his role in General Hospital and many fans are curious about the actor’s personal life in the wake of his sudden death. Here are all the details of his personal life and what happened to him. Did Johnny Wactor have a wife? No, John Wactor wasn’t married and didn’t have a wife. Wactor had always kept his personal life away from the public eye, making fans curious whether he was in a relationship or not. As per , in 2022, he was allegedly linked with Kaitlin Sullivan, following their posted close moments on his social media handle. The two never openly confirmed their low-key relationship. Their shared images also now seem to be deleted, indicating that they might have parted ways earlier. Moreover, it was reportedly known that he was single and was focused on his acting career before his untimely death. Johnny Wactor cause of death As per , Johnny Wactor died when he was shot by one of the three suspects who came to rob a vehicle’s catalytic converter on Saturday near Pica Boulevard and Hope Street. Wactor’s mother Scarlett spoke with and gave out details on what happened to her son. She revealed that he and his co-worker were returning from their bartending duties at a rooftop bar around 3 am or 3:30 am. That’s when they saw three men whom he thought were towing his car. However, when Wactor interrupted them, a masked man shot him. Wactor was quickly taken to a local hospital. However, it was too late by then and he didn’t survive. Johnny Wactor’s death was confirmed by his agent David Shaul in an official statement, released by Variety, where he shared his kind words. “Johnny Wactor was a spectacular human being. Not just a talented actor who was committed to his craft but a real moral example to everyone who knew him. Standing for hard work, tenacity and a never give up attitude. In the highs and lows of a challenging profession he always kept his chin up and kept striving for the best he could be. Our time with Johnny was a privilege we would wish on everyone. He would literally give you the shirt off his back. After over a decade together, he will leave a hole in our hearts forever,” Shaul said. The police have opened an investigation and are on the search for the three suspects, who ran away from the crime scene. Shazmeen is a writer, entertainment journalist, and movie aficionado at core. She holds a degree in multimedia and mass communication, specializing in advertising, but her ardor for cinema led her into entertainment journalism. While her cinematic preferences know no bounds, she specifically has fondness for the Marvel Cinematic Universe, psychological thrillers, horror, and films with profound philosophical undertones. title: Osun: Esa-Oke central union donates generator to community maternity centre
creator: Adeolu Adeyemo
description: Tribune OnlineOsun: Esa-Oke central union donates generator to community maternity centreThe executives of Esa-Oke Central Union in Osun State on Monday donated a generating set to the town maternity centre. The union also commissioned a renovated toilet for market women and cleared an eight-kilometre abandoned Imesi to Esa-Oke road. Speaking during the inauguration and swearing-in ceremony of executives, the union chairman, Gbamigboye Aremu said the [...]Osun: Esa-Oke central union donates generator to community maternity centreTribune Online
content: The executives of Esa-Oke Central Union in Osun State on Monday donated a generating set to the town maternity centre. The union also commissioned a renovated toilet for market women and cleared an eight-kilometre abandoned Imesi to Esa-Oke road. Speaking during the inauguration and swearing-in ceremony of executives, the union chairman, Gbamigboye Aremu said the gesture was to ease the affairs of the residents of the town. He said, “The reason why we donated the generating set was due to the complaint by those working in the maternity centre that they don’t usually get light during the delivery of pregnant women. “After the complaints, we the executives of the union tasked ourselves and get the generator for the maternity to aid their service delivery. “Also, the leadership of the market women came to us that they needed us to renovate their toilets for convenience which we also do. “We also cleared the bushy portion of Imesi to Esa-Oke road which has been abandoned by road users. Motorists are scared to pass the road for fear of being kidnapped but now, we have cleared the road and expanded it and our people can make use of it now.” Aremu appealed to the leadership of the community maternity centre and market to make proper use of the donated equipment and toilet. “I want to appeal to the beneficiaries to make proper use of the donated equipment. We have done our part and we are still aiming to do more but they also have to maintain those things judiciously .” The monarch of the town, Adeyemi Adediran, appreciated the union for their kind gesture, calling on sons and daughters of the community to always give back to their community. title: BoTT Collaborates With Meguru Yamaguchi in New Capsule Collection
creator: info@hypebeast.com (Hypebeast)
description: Birth of The Teenager (BoTT) has collaborated with Japanese-born, New York-based artist Meguru Yamaguchi on a limited capsule collection. Founded in 2019 by fellow Japanese artist TEITO, BoTT produces timeless streetwear staples using premium materials and playful graphics, which in the past has included collaborations with Umbro, TTTMSW and Reebok. Yamaguchi, who runs the Brooklyn-based studio and collective GOLD WOOD ARTWORKS, is known for creating dynamic abstract paintings that appear like an explosion of paint frozen in time. Notably inspired by the expressive works of Vincent Van Gogh and Kazuo Shiraga, over the past decade Yamaguchi has developed an aesthetic that is less about representation, and more an emphasis on the feeling of painting, as he super-sizes his brushstrokes into three-dimensional canvases and sculptures.BoTT and Yamaguchi created a line of simple branded tees, pillows and an ash tray bearing both the label's acronym overlaid on Yamaguchi's signature blue, black and white abstracted marks. title: Blue Kumuls, FC Genesis settle for 1-1 draw in fiery match-up
creator: pcAdminPNG
description: THE Blue Kumuls and FC Genesis clashed in a thrilling encounter that showcased the best of their skills, with both teams refusing to yield in the Port Moresby soccer association men's premier division match on Saturday.The post Blue Kumuls, FC Genesis settle for 1-1 draw in fiery match-up appeared first on Post Courier.
content: THE Blue Kumuls and FC Genesis clashed in a thrilling encounter that showcased the best of their skills, with both teams refusing to yield in the Port Moresby soccer association men’s premier division match on Saturday. In the end, they had to settle for a hard-fought draw, leaving both sets of fans eagerly anticipating their next showdown. Both teams wasted no time when five minutes from kickoff, Blue Kumuls were awarded a free kick just outside the penalty box. Hans Tapio (15) unleashed a powerful shot that ricocheted off the crossbar. After that, Genesis upped the ante, launching a sustained attack that yielded two successive corner kicks. Unfortunately, they couldn’t capitalise on the opportunities. Play continued in Genesis half of the field with Blue Kumuls midfield team of Steven Inia and Tapio probing the Genesis defence when a sneak pass found Jordan Kaven (11) who shot from within the box right on the 18th minute for Blue Kumuls to lead 1-0. A scramble in the Blue Kumul’s penalty box ten minutes later found Genesis number 16 Ezekiel Vela with a loose ball that he calmly pushed past keeper Baniau to level the scores at 1-1. The game’s intensity increased with the occasional push and shove that drew a couple of yellow cards to both sides. Blue Kumuls Inia occasionally tried using wide balls but was cut off by the defence of Nathan Togs and his company of youthful defenders for Genesis. Three minutes to half-time Genesis number 4, Stanley Kila picked up a missed ball by a Blue Kumuls defender only to miss what could have been the easiest of goals. Genesis came back in the second half all fired up with right winger Kaniyosi making his usual runs let loose a shot that hit the left post much to the delight of the supporters on the sidelines. Midfielders led by Benjamin Kila continued with their threatening runs into Blue Kumuls territory but the strikers time and again could not find the mark with their shots. Number 16 Vela made several attempts at goal but most were wide also. Niebo and Ara also made attempts for Genesis without much success. Ten minutes later a clearance header from a corner to Steven Inia found henchman Tapio who shot unchallenged from the edge of the box to just tip the crossbar. That miss brought deafening sighs to the Blue Kumuls supporters. Inia continued with his through balls when a pass landed in front of teammate Steven Giwibing (2) who fumbled right in the box much to the dismay of the sighing supporters. A minute to time Steven Inia was assisted off-field with an injury with the scores remaining at one all until full-time. Marty Terry of Blue Kumuls commented saying: “ We had our chances but could not finish off well. “And yes both teams played well also’’ Genesis’s Emmanuel Liosi said: “Blue Kumuls is a respected team in the premier division and when you play them you take them seriously. “Yes our youthful team did their best but we did miss a lot of chances also.”

title: Hunt for two men after double assault in Carnoustie leaves man in hospital
creator: Matthew Fulton
description: A 23-year-old was taken to Ninewells Hospital in Dundee to be treated for serious injuries.
content: Officers said two men, aged 23 and 30, were assaulted at around 12.30am in Carnoustie on Saturday, May 25 by two other men on Ferrier Street with the junction of Dundee Street. The 23-year-old was taken to Ninewells Hospital in Dundee to be treated for serious injuries, while the 30-year-old did not require medical treatment. Police are searching for two men, one of whom is described as in his late teens to early 20s, wearing a dark long sleeve top, grey trousers and white trainers. The second man is described as in his late teens to early 20s, of slim build, with short dark hair shaved at the sides, wearing a black T-shirt, black shorts, white socks and grey/black Nike trainers. Detective Constable Euan Mitchell of CID said: “This assault left one of the victims with serious injuries. “We know the area was busy at the time and I am asking anyone who witnessed the assault and has not already spoken to police to contact us. “If you believe you could help our enquiries, call quoting reference 0151 of May 25, 2024. “Alternatively, you can call Crimestoppers on , if you wish to remain anonymous.” Get all the latest news from around the country Scan the QR code on your mobile device for all the latest news from around the country

title: 'Did they think you were setting up a halting site?' - Man fumes on RTÉ radio as council take caravan
creator: Jasmin Griffin
description: A 71-year-old security guard, William Brown, was shocked to discover his caravan, purchased a month prior, was missing from his property after returning from his early morning shift. Speaking to Joe Duffy on RTÉ's Liveline, William, who starts work in Dublin at 5am, was informed one morning last wee
content: The caravan, which Mr Browne admits he acquired for €1,600 just four weeks ago, was to be intended as a cost-effective alternative to B&Bs and hotels Reporter: Reporter 27 May 2024 7:15 PM A 71-year-old security guard, William Browne, was shocked to discover his caravan, purchased a month prior, was missing from his property after returning from his early morning shift. Speaking to Joe Duffy on RTÉ's Liveline, William, who starts work in Dublin at 5am, was informed one morning last week by his daughter at approximately 10am that the caravan had been taken. It was confirmed that South Dublin County Council's Environmental team removed the caravan following several complaints from local residents. The caravan, which William admits he acquired for €1,600 just four weeks ago, was to be intended as a cost-effective alternative to B&Bs and hotels. Originally from Wexford, now living in Clondalkin, he said that he had planned to use the caravan for visits home, especially during summer when relatives come to visit. Despite words from council staff that the caravan was not an issue as long as it was unoccupied, William was surprised by the action taken against him. It is said that a notice citing the Housing Miscellaneous Provisions Act required him to remove the "temporary dwelling" within one day, with warnings of a €1,270 fine. The caravan, which they joked was something from 'Father Ted,' was on a grassy spot until it was seized. "There's an patch of grass, westbound, at the side of my house and there's surveillance there on the wall, and that's where the carvan was," said William. Later, Joe responded: " What did they think you were doing? Setting up a halting site or something." After calling the council's environmental office after receiving a letter regarding the caravan, William received no answer so took to visit the Tallaght-based office. It said that the situation remains unresolved, and the caravan is still seized. William, who also owns a small boat and a jeep which can pull the caravan, was disappointed over the council’s actions. Given previous health struggles which he detailed on the show, including past heart surgery, a stroke, diabetes, and chronic asthma, William told Joe of his worries on his health regarding the stress of the ordeal. South Dublin County Council have been contacted for comment on the matter, but had not replied at time of publication.

title: Katie Price shares savage post about 'narcissistic people' after Carl Woods split

content: Katie Price shared a post detailing 'five reasons the narcissist hates you' months after her split from Carl Woods. The former glamour model, who is currently dating Married At First Sight UK star JJ Slater, was previously engaged to Love Island star Carl. The duo were in an on-ff relationship since they first started dating in 2020. They were believed to have split up again in November last year but sparked reconciliation rumours the following month when they were seen together . Not long after, Katie was seen enjoying cosy nights out with JJ before confirming their relationship on social media. Katie, who doesn't shy away from sharing cryptic posts about her exes, recently took to her social media to share a post about narcissism on her Stories. The post read: "Five reasons the narcissist hates you: 1. You've stopped falling for their lies 2. They've lost the control they once had over you 3. You've cracked their facade and see them for who they really are 4. You're no longer desperate for their approval 5. Their schemes and tricks don't work on you anymore." Katie shared a new post about narcissism on her page ( Image: Instagram/ @katieprice) The duo, who were in an on-off relationship for a few years, split last year ( Image: Getty Images) Back in February, Carl made a few digs about the split as he praised himself for getting himself through the tough period. Carl vowed to keep a 'low profile' and focus on himself after the breakup. Taking to his Instagram stories, the former Love Island star made a number of digs at his ex-fiancée. In one story post, Carl showed off his adorable new puppy as he joked that his new pet pooch was 'doing his head in'. However, he also commended his dog's immense 'loyalty' as he said it was the 'most important thing'. In another story, Carl re-shared an inspirational video which said: "God knows when to send you exactly what you need. Being private, staying low-key, and not telling everyone everything is self-care. Seek respect, not attention." Carl then appeared to reference his split with Katie as he re-shared yet another inspirational video. "I love you enough to let you go," the video started. "Go find that person that you say is better than me. Everything hurts when you love somebody. I love for real." Meanwhile, Carl and Katie's other ex Kieran Hayler united at Silver Leas Polo in Hertfordshire and looked all smiles as they shared a video of their outing on social media. However, one of their mutual pals present couldn't help but point out the meeting was "awkward", while jokingly putting a hand to their mouth as the camera panned around. This isn't the first time Kieran and Carl spend time together as they previously celebrated Easter Sunday as a duo - which allegedly left their famous ex furious.
